{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/rbdconvexproxy", "tags": "rigidbodies"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["RBD Convex Proxy"], "extent": [48, 69]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a number of rigid bodies from SOP geometry, which use proxy geometry from a convex decomposition."], "extent": [69, 183]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [183, 198], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool uses the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition", "type": "link", "text": ["Convex Decomposition SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition"}, " to generate proxy geometry for the RBD objects. A compound collision shape built from several convex hulls can be much faster to simulate for concave geometry."], "extent": [198, 435]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool is similar to the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Sphere Proxy tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy"}, " on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Rigid Bodies"]}, " shelf. However, instead of using proxy geometry composed of spheres, it preserves hard edges and creates more accurate shapes. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Sphere Proxy tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy"}, " is very lightweight and fast, which is useful for background objects where you don\u2019t mind rounded out corners as a tradeoff for speed. Convex Decomposition is useful for more complex or foreground objects with many hard edges."], "extent": [435, 934]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/rbdconvexproxy.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [934, 976]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using RBD Convex Proxy"], "extent": [976, 1017], "body": [{"ty